Is /redfish/v1/Chassis/chassis/ThermalSubsystem/Fans/fan2_0 rotor 0 of fan 2?

> I am confused by this statement, don't you just display all the fans with the cooled_by association from the chassis? I am confused how/why you would treat dual-rotor differently? Is a dual-rotor fan, 1 or 2 Redfish endpoints?

For all fans, some fans are single rotor, some fans are dual rotor.
eg:
Single rotor: fan0
Dual rotor: fan0/fan0_0 & fan0/fan0_1
But the association between the fan and the chassis is fan0 and chassis, not fan0/fan0_0 and chassis
So we can judge whether the current fan is a dual-rotor through the association between fan and sensor(https://github.com/ibm-openbmc/openbmc/blob/1030.00/meta-ibm/recipes-phosphor/inventory/phosphor-inventory-manager/p10bmc/ibm%2Crainier-4u_associations.json#L19-L27).


> Is /redfish/v1/Chassis/chassis/ThermalSubsystem/Fans/fan2_0 rotor 0 of fan 2?

Yes, and fan2_1 is rotor 1 of fan 2.
I have updated the commit to retrieve all fans associated with the chassis by utilizing the 'cooled_by' association.
